Privacy Policy for Uptimecoding
At https://uptimecoding.blogspot.com/?m=1, accessible from https://uptimecoding.blogspot.com/?m=1, one of our main priorities is the privacy of our visitors. This Privacy Policy document contains types of information that is collected and recorded by https://uptimecoding.blogspot.com/?m=1 and how we use it.

If you have additional questions or require more information about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us.

This Privacy Policy applies only to our online activities and is valid for visitors to our website with regards to the information that they shared and/or collect in https://uptimecoding.blogspot.com/?m=1. This policy is not applicable to any information collected offline or via channels other than this website.

Consent
By using our website, you hereby consent to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.

Information we collect
The personal information that you are asked to provide, and the reasons why you are asked to provide it, will be made clear to you at the point we ask you to provide your personal information.

If you contact us directly, we may receive additional information about you such as your name, email address, phone number, the contents of the message and/or attachments you may send us, and any other information you may choose to provide.

When you register for an Account, we may ask for your contact information, including items such as name, company name, address, email address, and telephone number.



User Image Uploading Policy:



Uptimecoding allows users to upload images to the website for various purposes, such as profile pictures, avatars, or content submissions. We value the privacy and safety of our users, including the protection of their personal information. Therefore, we have implemented the following user image uploading policy:



Consent: By uploading an image to Uptimecoding, you agree to our Privacy Policy and the terms outlined in this user image uploading policy.



Personal Image Usage: When you upload an image to Uptimecoding, please be aware that personal images, such as profile pictures or avatars, may be visible to other users of the website. We recommend avoiding the upload of sensitive or private images that you do not wish to share publicly.



Ownership and Responsibility: You are solely responsible for the images you upload to Uptimecoding. Please ensure that you have the necessary rights and permissions to use and upload the images. Uptimecoding does not claim ownership of the images uploaded by users.



Prohibited Content: Users are strictly prohibited from uploading images that contain explicit, offensive, illegal, or copyrighted content. Any image that violates these guidelines will be removed, and appropriate actions may be taken against the user, including account suspension or termination.



Security: Uptimecoding implements reasonable security measures to protect user-uploaded images from unauthorized access or misuse. However, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of user images. Therefore, we recommend not uploading images containing sensitive or confidential information.



Image Removal: If you wish to have an uploaded image removed from Uptimecoding, please contact us using the provided contact information in our Privacy Policy. We will make reasonable efforts to promptly remove the image as per your request.



Children's Images: Uptimecoding does not knowingly collect or allow the uploading of personal images of children under the age of 13. If you believe that an image of a child under the age of 13 has been uploaded without proper consent, please contact us immediately, and we will take appropriate actions to remove it.

